<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Windsurfer Arrested,0171</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman Arrested For Fleeing Marine Patrol On Sailboard</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STUART, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 54-year-old windsurfer was arrested and
booked into jail in a wet bathing suit after she allegedly tried to
use her board to make a getaway from a Florida Marine Patrol
officer.
   Jean Felicia Kuznar, of Jensen Beach, was charged with careless
operation of a vessel, interfering with navigation, resisting
arrest without violence, and fleeing and eluding law officers.
   Her problems with Officer Leslie Jones began when Mrs. Kuznar
was windsurfing Wednesday near the Stuart Causeway and a powerboat
entered the channel.
   Ms. Jones said the powerboat had to ``take evasive action to
avoid an accident,'' so she approached Mrs. Kuznar in her patrol
boat to discuss the matter.
   Ms. Jones said Mrs. Kuznar refused orders that she bring her
windsurfer to shore and ``told me to get lost.''
   Mrs. Kuznar said she was trying to get to shore, and complained
that the officer swamped her with the patrol boat's wake.
</TEXT>
