<DATELINE>HYANNIS PORT, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kennedy family members gathered at
the clan's seaside homes here to celebrate the 98th birthday of
matriarch Rose Kennedy.
   The family celebration began Friday with Mass and then moved to
the compound for dinner. The party concluded with white cake with
chocolate frosting, which Mrs. Kennedy's daughter Jean Smith said
is her mother's favorite.
   Mrs. Kennedy's only living son, Sen. Edward M. Kennedy, D-Mass.,
flew to Cape Cod for the occasion as soon as the Democratic
National Convention in Atlanta concluded.
   For her grandmother, Kara Kennedy, the senator's daughter,
picked 98 long-stemmed red roses from the Rose Kennedy Garden in
Boston's North End, where Mrs. Kennedy was born.
   Others at the dinner were Mrs. Kennedy's daughter Eunice and
son-in-law Sargent Shriver, daughters Patricia Lawford and Mrs.
Smith, daughter-in-law Ethel Kennedy and an assortment of
grandchildren.
   Mrs. Kennedy suffered a stroke in 1984 and reportedly has been
in poor health recently.
