   A trial involving a child custody battle
between actor Peter O'Toole and a New Jersey woman has ended, and
the Superior Court judge who heard the case says he might issue a
decision next week.
   The trial before Judge Alexander Lehrer was closed to reporters
shortly after it began July 13. It ended Thursday.
   Five-year-old Lorcan O'Toole has been caught in a trans-Atlantic
tussle between his father and Karen Somerville O'Toole since the
couple separated in 1983.
   A New Jersey court gave the couple joint custody in an agreement
lasting until September 1989. But both sides argued for a change in
that agreement.
   In May, a judge in London ordered O'Toole to return his son to
Ms. Somerville O'Toole until the courts decide which parent should
get permanent custody.
   Attorneys say O'Toole and Ms. Somerville O'Toole _ who was not
married to the actor but took his name _ claim each violated the
original custody agreement. Under it, each parent was to alternate
custody every month until 1989, when they hoped to reach a
long-term agreement.
   The Irish-born O'Toole, 55, met Ms. Somerville O'Toole, a
37-year-old former model, six years ago.
