<HEAD>___</HEAD>
<HEAD>Teamsters Lawyer Replaced</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   James T. Grady of Boston has been named
general counsel of the Teamsters, replacing John R. Climaco who was
closely aligned with the late union president Jackie Presser, the
union announced.
   William J. McCarthy, the Teamsters' new president, said in a
statement issued Friday, ``I have known Jim Grady for many years.
He is one of the finest labor lawyers in the nation, and he will be
a tremendous asset to me and the Teamsters Union.''
   Grady, a prominent labor lawyer, represents McCarthy's home
base, Local 25.
   The New York Times reported the ostensible reason for Climaco's
dismissal is that he had not provided a more vigorous defense of
the Teamsters in the face of an intense assault by the Justice
Department on the union's activities.
