<HEAD>Two Killed In Clash Over Shrimp Cultivation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A clash between villagers and police
over a shrimp cultivation project resulted in the death of a
policeman and a schoolteacher, police said Saturday.
   Police Friday fired into a crowd of more than 2,000 villagers
who were trying to tear down a dam built to contain water for
cultivating shrimp, police said. They said the schoolteacher was
killed in the skirmish.
   About 50 people were injured and at least 20 were hospitalized,
police said.
   The villagers, angered by the teacher's death, later beat to
death a police officer, officials said, speaking on condition of
anonymity.
   Residents of the village of Dinna, about 60 miles southwest of
the capital of Dhaka, claimed the dam was flooding large areas of
fertile land and destroying crops.
