<HEAD>Eight Killed, Five Injured In Mudslide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eight people were killed and five were
injured Saturday when a mudslide crushed their huts in northeast
Bombay, the United News of India reported.
   The agency said a small hill in the Ghatkopar neighborhood of
the city gave way and crushed four huts.
   The agency said four of the injured were children. It said they
were treated at a local hospital and released. A fifth victim was
hospitalized with fractures, it said.
   Landslides have been reported throughout northern India since
the annual monsoon rains began in late June.
