<1ST_LINE>r a AM-SkullsFound     07-23 0378</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Skulls Found,0389</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Murder Charges Filed In Death Of Man Whose Skull Was Buried</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Note contents.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man has been charged with murder three
months after the decomposing head of a former boarder was found
buried in his backyard.
   Robert A. Berdella was named in a first-degree murder indictment
issued Friday by a Jackson County grand jury. He is accused of
murdering Larry W. Pearson, of Wichita, Kan.
   Authorities said additional charges are pending against Berdella
in the death of a second man whose skull was found in Berdella's
house.
   Berdella, 39, was arrested April 2 after a man wearing only a
dog collar fled from Berdella's home, saying he had been held
captive for four days and had been subjected to sexual abuse and
torture.
   Berdella was charged with seven counts of forcible sodomy, one
of felonious restrain and one of assault in that case. He is being
held on $750,000 bond each for the murder charge and the sexual
torture charges.
   Pearson's skull was found in a shallow grave the day after
Berdella was arrested. Pearson apparently had rented a room for a
time in Berdella's house, family members said. He would have been
21 in February.
   ``We had some forensic evidence, we had some medical evidence
and a good deal of police testimony,'' Jackson County Prosecutor
Albert Riederer said of what led to the grand jury indictment.
   Pearson died six weeks to six months before police found his
skull, according to an anthropologist's findings filed in court.
   Analysis of Pearson's skull showed that the fifth vertebra, from
just above the base of his neck, had been cut several times by a
saw. The cuts were made ``while the deceased was still alive or
shortly after death,'' according to court documents.
   Police seized two circular saws, a hacksaw, a miter saw, a
disassembled jigsaw, 14 jigsaw blades, knives, scissors and
clippers from Berdella's house, according to search warrants.
   Charges in the death of another man, Robert Sheldon, whose skull
was found in Berdella's house, are pending, said Riederer.
   Sheldon was a 23-year-old California man. His skull was found in
a bedroom closet in Berdella's house. Police also found pieces of
backbone and two envelopes of teeth in the closet.
</TEXT>
