<HEAD>Storm Damages Shopping Center, Injures 16</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TORCY, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hail, torrential rains and strong winds
smashed windows and damaged the roof of a shopping center in this
Paris suburb Saturday, injuring 16 people, officials said.
   No deaths were reported, but damage to the Continent shopping
complex was extensive. Fire officials said one person was seriously
injured and 15 suffered less serious injuries.
   Witnesses said hail ``as big as small eggs'' fell on the
shopping center. Most of the injured were hit with shards of glass,
fire officials said.
   Heavy showers swept through the Paris region late Saturday,
accompanied by lightning and wind that tore off roofs and uprooted
trees around Torcy, about 20 miles east of Paris.
