<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Italy-MayorKilled     07-23 0147</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Italy-Mayor Killed,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mayor Slain After Stormy Town Council Meeting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLZATE, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gas station owner who was enraged by the
town council's refusal to give him a car-wash permit shot and
killed the mayor of this northern Italian village and then
committed suicide, police said Saturday.
   Authorities said Marino Cotter, 58, shouted at Mayor Luigi
Rodigari during a town council meeting Friday night and left the
building only after officials threatened to call police.
   Colzate is a town of about 1,600 people, 50 miles north of Milan.
   After the meeting, Cotter, 58, approached the car in which the
46-year-old mayor was sitting in the parking lot, threw open the
door and fired 13 times with a pistol, police said.
   Cotter also shot the driver, Fernando Bonfanti, who heads the
local chapter of the Christian Democrat party, police said. He was
in serious condition.
</TEXT>
