<HEAD>Three Cars of Train Derail; Two Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FOLIGNO, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three cars of an express passenger train
derailed near this central Italian city Saturday, injuring a
British student and an Italian man, authorities said.
   The derailment was apparently caused by overheated train tracks,
police said.
   The five-car Florence-Foligno train jumped the tracks near
Cannara, about 125 miles north of Rome.
   Two people were treated at the Foligno hospital _ Walter
Pirotta, 48, of Cinisello Balsamo, Italy and Jane Westwell, 20, a
student in Perugia. Her hometown in England was not immediately
available.
   They suffered whiplash and were released shortly after treatment.
</TEXT>
