<HEAD>Canadian Police Prepare for Bikers' Bash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NANAIMO, British Columbia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Authorities warned thousands of
motorcyclists not to party too hard when they rumble into town for
a grand bash next weekend.
   About 5,000 bikers were expected at the party on Vancouver
Island off Canada's Pacific coast. Last year's gathering of about
2,000 enthusiasts drew local complaints about noisy motorcycles.
